column5: See the cycles, learn the lessons. Don't try, just feel, don't hate, respect all, don't attach, be present. Right?
Why change something amazing and meaningful?
To be free is to be God?
To be free of the concept of time and space as separate from us?
To do everything you planned to do in this lifetime?
To be able to do everything you want to do and be yourself before you release the body?
What's it like to be free?
Yes, I've experienced his teachings before. This sermon is very condensed and to the point. Thanks sgain.
Loved it again. Is so good. Very good.
I like the way he expresses his joy. Must watch again.
Thank you for sharing. Will watch now.
What would it be like to be all imagination?
You have good awareness of the dual nature of mind. And you know you are not that. May you be pure joy.
All in the imagination... you're welcome. Enjoy.
Are you pure joy, happiness, silence, zero fears, abundance and beauty then?
“To attempt to change circumstances before you change your imaginal activity, is to struggle against the very nature of things.” -Neville Goddard
What would it be like if you were the ultimate?
Great that N.M's quotes resonated with you to awaken. I acknowledge you for acknowledging your true self.
I don't N.M. but seems like someone who cares. What would it be like if you were identifying with Brahman and not separate from?
There is no we really. It identifies with itself and Awakens.
Love is a bridge between mind and Soul... hence spiritual awakening and Oneness beyond words.

It's always just you... jk. Peace. Yes, this is a very spiritually developmental time for most of humanity. A break in habitual body and thought patterns naturally reveals the Soul. Truth from stillness...
There is only death in the body. The mind is both life and death, creation and reaction. Spirit is deathless.
